        public GeocodeServiceResponse geocode(java.lang.String datapackBundle,
                             java.lang.String country,
                             java.lang.String placeName,
                             java.lang.String mainAddress,
                             java.lang.String lastLine,
                             java.lang.String areaName1,
                             java.lang.String areaName2,
                             java.lang.String areaName3,
                             java.lang.String areaName4,
                             java.lang.Integer postalCode,
                             java.lang.String matchMode,
                             java.lang.Boolean fallbackGeo,
                             java.lang.Boolean fallbackPostal,
                             java.lang.Integer maxCands,
                             java.lang.Integer streetOffset,
                             java.lang.String streetOffsetUnits,
                             java.lang.Integer cornerOffset,
                             java.lang.String cornerOffsetUnits)
                               throws ApiException
        Gets Geocode Gets Geocode
        Parameters:
        datapackBundle - value of datapackBundle (required)
        country - Country name or ISO code. (optional, default to USA)
        placeName - Building name, place name, Point of Interest (POI), company or firm name associated with the input address. (optional)
        mainAddress - Single line input, treated as collection of field elements. (optional, default to 4750 Walnut St., Boulder CO, 80301)
        lastLine - The last line of the address. (optional)
        areaName1 - Specifies the largest geographic area, typically a state or province. (optional)
        areaName2 - Specifies the secondary geographic area, typically a county or district. (optional)
        areaName3 - Specifies a city or town name. (optional)
        areaName4 - Specifies a city subdivision or locality. (optional)
        postalCode - The postal code in the appropriate format for the country. (optional)
        matchMode - Match modes determine the leniency used to make a match between the input address and the reference data. (optional, default to Standard)
        fallbackGeo - Specifies whether to attempt to determine a geographic region centroid when an address-level geocode cannot be determined. (optional, default to true)
        fallbackPostal - Specifies whether to attempt to determine a post code centroid when an address-level geocode cannot be determined. (optional, default to true)
        maxCands - The maximum number of candidates to return. Must be an integer value. (optional, default to 1)
        streetOffset - Indicates the offset distance from the street segments to use in street-level geocoding. (optional, default to 7)
        streetOffsetUnits - Specifies the unit of measurement for the street offset. (optional, default to METERS)
        cornerOffset - Specifies the distance to offset the street end points in street-level matching. (optional, default to 7)
        cornerOffsetUnits - Specifies the unit of measurement for the corner offset. (optional, default to METERS)
        Returns:
        GeocodeServiceResponse
        Throws:
        ApiException - If fail to call the API, e.g. server error or cannot deserialize the response body
